cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CG 

This paper deals with path planning for walking characters in virtual environments, which is a common problem in computer graphics and robotics. The paper proposes a new navigation mesh based on the medial axis, which is a well-known concept in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), followed by cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves image processing and machine learning techniques to annotate the medial axis with obstacle information, which suggests the categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic approach to construct the medial axis, which falls under the category cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
